1
00:00:04,440 --> 00:00:05,779
The long-awaited three-month-long journey...

2
00:00:05,780 --> 00:00:08,250
- Let's go. - of Bake Your Dream.

3
00:00:09,250 --> 00:00:10,380
The final competition.

4
00:00:12,050 --> 00:00:13,490
It's Bread as a Meal.

5
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,300
Keep the theme in mind.

6
00:00:27,530 --> 00:00:29,930
The bread has to stand out.

7
00:00:30,070 --> 00:00:33,070
- It has to be tasty. - Or you're in trouble.

8
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:36,540
It's getting hotter.

9
00:00:37,540 --> 00:00:39,310
The chefs are watching from the back.

10
00:00:41,180 --> 00:00:42,180
Seriously.

11
00:00:42,610 --> 00:00:45,079
- Chef Lee Won Il is put in early. - Yes.

12
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:47,049
Why was he brought in early?

13
00:00:47,050 --> 00:00:48,689
Is there a reason for it?

14
00:00:48,690 --> 00:00:50,789
- He's starting with the stuffing... - Is there?

15
00:00:50,790 --> 00:00:52,190
That needs to go inside the bread.

16
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:53,689
- When you're making bread, - Yes.

17
00:00:53,690 --> 00:00:54,959
You spend the latter 100 minutes...

18
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,290
- for baking. - That's right.

19
00:00:56,730 --> 00:00:58,690
They'll get the flavors right from the beginning.

20
00:00:59,130 --> 00:01:02,470
Korean food may require lots of time to prepare the ingredients.

21
00:01:23,690 --> 00:01:25,060
Look at the flame!

22
00:01:27,490 --> 00:01:29,129
With the cooking chefs,

23
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:30,610
we get to see a fire show. It's nice.

24
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,060
It's fun to watch.

25
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:36,270
- He's so serious right now. - Yes. He's serious.

26
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:44,180
It looks like chili paste.

27
00:01:44,410 --> 00:01:47,649
Doesn't it look like seasoning because of the chilis?

28
00:01:47,650 --> 00:01:48,850
Yes. It's Korean.

29
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:53,049
Personally, I don't want them to take risks.

30
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:54,549
He has never done something...

31
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:56,789
- that was safe. - You need to play it safe now.

32
00:01:56,790 --> 00:01:58,510
- He has always tried something new. - Yes.

33
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:04,490
- Those are blue crabs. - I can't believe it.

34
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:10,010
Is he using the crab meat?

35
00:02:12,670 --> 00:02:14,909
- That must be really tasty. - Hold on. That looks tasty.

36
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:15,940
It looks good.

37
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,609
It would taste good on its own.

38
00:02:18,610 --> 00:02:20,380
It'd be tasty to have that much.

39
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,450
It's hard to tell.

40
00:02:22,650 --> 00:02:23,720
Because it's culinary.

41
00:02:23,950 --> 00:02:28,050
The key concept to my Bread as a Meal is...

42
00:02:28,220 --> 00:02:29,290
"a rice thief."

43
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:33,860
We called the marinated crab a rice thief.

44
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:39,130
I'll fill up the bread with the marinated crab.

45
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,030
With the marinated crab?

46
00:02:41,570 --> 00:02:43,130
He's going bold again.

47
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,839
The marinated crab smells fishy, though.

48
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,210
You can't have it raw.

49
00:02:47,740 --> 00:02:49,640
- Won't he cook it, though? - He will, right?

50
00:02:51,110 --> 00:02:54,310
I won't put raw crab meat in the bread.

51
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:58,379
To get the texture of the squeezed crab meat,

52
00:02:58,380 --> 00:03:00,620
we made a paste mixture with the crab meat.

53
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:18,140
What on earth is the red thing?

54
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:21,409
He's mixing it with the stir-fried seasoning.

55
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:23,040
He added the stir-fried shrimp.

56
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,150
Taste it.

57
00:03:30,420 --> 00:03:33,250
The ratio is 1 to 1.5.

58
00:03:34,990 --> 00:03:36,430
- You can add a little more. - Okay.

59
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:39,859
He created the flavor I imagined...

60
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:42,189
right on the spot,

61
00:03:42,190 --> 00:03:43,700
so it was very interesting.

62
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:48,970
It's a taste you can only find in Korean food.

63
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:53,370
It'd be brilliant if we could make it into bread.

64
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:00,310
- Will it be a tart? - Right.

65
00:04:00,980 --> 00:04:01,980
A tart?

66
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:05,420
He'll add Korean ingredients in the tarts.

67
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:15,930
In the crunchy shell,

68
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:18,700
I'll put the marinated crab mousse.

69
00:04:19,260 --> 00:04:20,800
I'll make stir-fried crab meat...

70
00:04:20,970 --> 00:04:22,770
and souffle dough.

71
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:29,210
The conventional souffles are sweet.

72
00:04:29,870 --> 00:04:31,980
But I got rid of sugar for this one.

73
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:35,979
I'll add the Grana Padano cheese...

74
00:04:35,980 --> 00:04:38,350
for umami and soft flavor.

75
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:43,250
That's the kick to bring everything into harmony.

76
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:54,529
I heard Contender Ju Young Seok has chosen the Korean food.

77
00:04:54,530 --> 00:04:56,670
I don't think his will be similar to mine.

78
00:04:57,440 --> 00:05:00,469
I don't think anyone can come up...

79
00:05:00,470 --> 00:05:02,840
with an idea to use the marinated crab.

80
00:05:04,710 --> 00:05:07,880
Both of them are using Korean food, but in a totally different style.

81
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,820
Theirs is casual Korean food.

82
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:14,750
They are more on the traditional side.

83
00:05:20,660 --> 00:05:22,959
Contender Ju Young Seok has brought ttukbaegi.

84
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:24,200
They're authentic ttukbaegi.

85
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:33,200
Can you bake bread with ttukbaegi?

86
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:36,669
People make castella with ttukbaegi as a mold.

87
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:38,240
- Is that so? - Really? Goodness.

88
00:05:38,980 --> 00:05:40,310
It's a great idea.

89
00:05:40,650 --> 00:05:43,550
I've prepared a dining table.

90
00:05:44,180 --> 00:05:47,090
It won't be too heavy when you eat them together.

91
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:50,590
The concept is to make food that is easy to digest.

92
00:05:50,860 --> 00:05:54,060
I thought it would be a hearty Bread as a Meal.

93
00:05:56,030 --> 00:05:58,230
Because I'm portraying rice,

94
00:05:59,330 --> 00:06:01,769
I made the dough with a nurungji starter.

95
00:06:01,770 --> 00:06:04,469
I used the scorched rice water, instead of water.

96
00:06:04,470 --> 00:06:06,839
So, I made the focaccia...

97
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:09,069
into a bowl of rice...

98
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:10,880
that tastes like light nurungji.

99
00:06:21,220 --> 00:06:24,059
Chef Cho Seo Hyung,

100
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:25,159
did he use rice?

101
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,720
- He put the rice in. - I knew it.

102
00:06:27,390 --> 00:06:28,690
We use rice.

103
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:31,559
As for the oil for baking,

104
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,759
we made nurungji...

105
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:33,969
- with Golden Queen rice. - The Golden Queen, of course.

106
00:06:33,970 --> 00:06:35,099
- Number Three? - We extracted oil from it.

107
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:36,129
Golden Queen Number Three.

108
00:06:36,130 --> 00:06:38,169
So it'd taste like pot-cooked rice as soon as you eat it.

109
00:06:38,170 --> 00:06:39,470
- It tastes flavorful. - Yes.

110
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,610
Gosh. You've done your homework.

111
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:57,320
What is that?

112
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:02,889
- Is that kimchi? - Isn't it white kimchi?

113
00:07:02,890 --> 00:07:04,410
- I think it's dongchimi. - Dongchimi.

114
00:07:05,930 --> 00:07:08,100
- Bamboo shoots! - Bamboo shoots?

115
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:17,140
- What are those? - Soaked wild aster leaves.

116
00:07:19,740 --> 00:07:21,779
Does he have to prepare each leaf of them?

117
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:23,850
Yes. Otherwise, it'd be too tough to chew.

118
00:07:24,550 --> 00:07:25,749
Korean food requires so much preparation.

119
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,290
Yes. It requires so much prep.

120
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:30,860
It seems they'd make Korean food with several side dishes.

121
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:32,490
You can tell there is so much to do.

122
00:07:37,930 --> 00:07:39,930
- What are those? - They're Korean mints.

123
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:41,580
Why are there so many vegetables?

124
00:07:41,770 --> 00:07:43,430
He's making real Korean food.

125
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:46,770
It's "Korean Food War" over here.

126
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:53,340
- Pine nuts. - Are they pine nuts?

127
00:07:58,820 --> 00:08:01,290
- Chestnuts. - Is he using chestnuts?

128
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:04,770
Contender Ju Young Seok is using so many ingredients.

129
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:07,230
He'll spend all his time preparing the ingredients.

130
00:08:07,430 --> 00:08:09,129
The chef should have started it. Don't you think?

131
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:10,489
They should have...

132
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,330
because there are many ingredients to prepare.

133
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:14,670
Chef, are the chestnuts cooked?

134
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:17,100
- Yes, they're good. - They're good?

135
00:08:23,210 --> 00:08:25,110
Is he smashing the dried persimmons?

136
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,280
Goodness.

137
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,629
Why doesn't he use a bigger spoon?

138
00:08:46,630 --> 00:08:47,630
Exactly.

139
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:49,470
Like a wooden spatula.

140
00:08:55,810 --> 00:08:57,339
I tried to do as much prep...

141
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:59,780
as possible before Chef Cho Seo Hyung steps in.

142
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:01,649
But I saw my limits.

143
00:09:01,650 --> 00:09:03,549
I wanted her to come.

144
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:04,920
That was what I was thinking.

145
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:07,849
Contender Ju Young Seok...

146
00:09:07,850 --> 00:09:09,420
keeps looking at Chef Cho Seo Hyung...

147
00:09:09,820 --> 00:09:10,890
asking for help.

148
00:09:15,730 --> 00:09:16,760
You can do it.

149
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:43,249
I told him...

150
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:46,160
to put the bamboo shoots in a strain.

151
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:49,890
But he kept them in water.

152
00:09:50,060 --> 00:09:51,199
At a glance,

153
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,259
I could tell the flavorful taste...

154
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:55,270
of the bamboo shoots has disappeared.

155
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:05,110
I'm curious about Team Thai.

156
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:09,310
It's not an easy cuisine to make into bread.

157
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,120
Careful.

158
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:25,630
Contender Kim Jin Seok took out the dough...

159
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:27,946
- from the pastry roller. - He's rolling the dough.

160
00:10:27,970 --> 00:10:29,430
But the color is...

161
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:32,500
Did he put curry powder? I don't think so.

162
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:34,109
- I think so. - Tumeric?

163
00:10:34,110 --> 00:10:35,770
- Paprika? - It's Thai food.

164
00:10:36,270 --> 00:10:37,540
Something like Thai curry?

165
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:43,310
Our team is making Poo Pad Pong Bread Curry.

166
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:55,230
People are familiar with the dish.

167
00:10:55,290 --> 00:10:57,559
I thought of making it different...

168
00:10:57,560 --> 00:11:00,700
by making it into bread.

169
00:11:05,070 --> 00:11:08,539
I think you should taste it.

170
00:11:08,540 --> 00:11:09,570
Thank you.

171
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:12,710
Goodness. It's crazy.

172
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:20,079
It's exactly the style I like.

173
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,090
- Is that so? - Yes.

174
00:11:21,820 --> 00:11:25,659
Why don't we make curry like this?

175
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:26,890
I love it.

176
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:30,960
When I tried Chef Kim Yu Ah's curry,

177
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,170
I thought it was a done deal.

178
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:39,439
I thought of adding ham to it.

179
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:42,170
- I think it's a good idea. - So I brought it today.

180
00:11:47,450 --> 00:11:50,080
I'll top the crab with the ham to finish.

181
00:11:51,180 --> 00:11:52,780
Okay. Please try it.

182
00:12:00,390 --> 00:12:01,790
- It's tasty. - It tastes familiar.

183
00:12:03,660 --> 00:12:06,629
I found out the amount of sodium...

184
00:12:06,630 --> 00:12:08,530
is less in this product.

185
00:12:08,630 --> 00:12:09,830
I think it's good.

186
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:12,200
It goes well with the curry.

187
00:12:12,970 --> 00:12:14,970
It has the garlic taste too.

188
00:12:15,240 --> 00:12:18,110
I think the umami is from Euiseong garlic.

189
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:20,210
- It's tasty. - It's good.

190
00:12:21,810 --> 00:12:25,420
I love savory bread the most.

191
00:12:25,780 --> 00:12:28,320
So, I'm super confident.

192
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:34,860
I don't know what he's making.

193
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:47,400
To make the bread the center of attention,

194
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:51,410
I made crab shells for the Poo Pad Pong Curry.

195
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:06,820
He's making the crab shapes.

196
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:09,330
- Are they crab shapes? - Yes.

197
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:12,700
- He's making the crab shells. - I see.

198
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,700
Contender Kim Jin Seo is good...

199
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:23,309
at getting the design right.

200
00:13:23,310 --> 00:13:24,610
- Yes. - You're right.

201
00:13:24,810 --> 00:13:27,910
He looks rustic, but he's actually meticulous.

202
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:32,419
He won the Skills Competitions.

203
00:13:32,420 --> 00:13:34,389
- So, he's good... - He's good at shaping.

204
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:35,890
At doing that stuff.

205
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:39,960
What is Chef Yu Ah's team doing?

206
00:13:40,690 --> 00:13:42,460
They're being creative.

207
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:52,700
Contender Kim Jin Seo. Yes.

208
00:13:54,310 --> 00:13:56,640
- They're crab shells. - Those are crab bodies.

209
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,980
What? He's putting the dough on something.

210
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:07,950
Is he making the crab eyes?

211
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:11,659
Gosh. Contender Kim Jin Seo is so good with the details.

212
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,820
He's serious when it comes to details.

213
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:18,660
They look like real crabs.

214
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:19,830
They're pretty.

215
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:23,190
I wonder how they'll turn out once they're baked.

216
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:41,290
- They're blue crabs. - Gosh. They have eyes now.

217
00:14:42,790 --> 00:14:44,220
What a crab.

218
00:14:46,890 --> 00:14:49,460
Wait. That sounded like...

219
00:14:50,960 --> 00:14:51,960
Crabs.

220
00:14:51,961 --> 00:14:53,800
- They look like crabs. - Crabs.

221
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,630
You didn't swear, did you?

222
00:14:56,830 --> 00:14:57,970
They're like crabs.

223
00:15:07,910 --> 00:15:10,949
They only have three hours.

224
00:15:10,950 --> 00:15:12,349
- Yes. Three hours. - So...

225
00:15:12,350 --> 00:15:14,790
Many will make pastries.

226
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:19,560
The savory bread goes well with pastries.

227
00:15:20,860 --> 00:15:23,030
Why did everyone choose pastries?

228
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:27,200
I wouldn't be able to make good-quality pastries in time.

229
00:15:30,070 --> 00:15:32,770
I thought I'd make bread.

230
00:15:34,970 --> 00:15:38,109
I thought the straight dough would be a safe choice.

231
00:15:38,110 --> 00:15:41,780
But the straight dough shouldn't be too light.

232
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:43,149
It should incorporate skills.

233
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:45,080
It should have flavors.

234
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:46,679
It's because it's hard...

235
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:49,390
to satisfy the refined palate of the Masters.

236
00:15:53,060 --> 00:15:54,729
In the end, what's important for us...

237
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:56,689
is how well the bread is baked.

238
00:15:56,690 --> 00:15:59,660
Yes. That's the title of the mission.

239
00:15:59,830 --> 00:16:01,399
It should be well-made.

240
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:05,869
It'd be good to add something to the well-made bread.

241
00:16:05,870 --> 00:16:08,240
I think it'll be nice...

242
00:16:08,470 --> 00:16:11,040
if we can find that something among ingredients.

243
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:14,650
If they're the ingredients from Jeju Island...

244
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:16,910
- Okay. - My mother is haenyeo, the diver.

245
00:16:18,150 --> 00:16:19,150
Yes.

246
00:16:19,151 --> 00:16:20,180
What?

247
00:16:20,650 --> 00:16:23,189
I thought it'd be only appropriate...

248
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:26,960
to use it as a keyword for this mission.

249
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:30,089
Contender Kim Si Yeob's childhood...

250
00:16:30,090 --> 00:16:32,530
and the story of his mother.

251
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:35,470
How are we going to portray those as bread?

252
00:16:36,170 --> 00:16:38,270
I think it'll feel like Jeju Island again.

253
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:39,870
It's time for basalt.

254
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:44,380
It's Basalt Bread that symbolizes Jeju Island.

255
00:16:46,410 --> 00:16:48,650
It's the place my mother can catch her breath.

256
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:52,650
It's a place where she can rest while working in the garden.

257
00:16:54,420 --> 00:16:57,620
That's what basalt has been to my mother.

258
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,480
He's going to make basalt with it.

259
00:17:01,790 --> 00:17:02,960
The ink.

260
00:17:09,230 --> 00:17:11,239
- The dough came out great. - Look how bouncy it is.

261
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,970
- It's so bouncy. - Yes.

262
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:15,869
I can tell it'll be chewy even from here.

263
00:17:15,870 --> 00:17:17,010
He's satisfied.

264
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:28,120
