01:25:17,120 --> 01:25:19,950
and made curry sauce by grinding it up ourselves...

1313
01:25:20,290 --> 01:25:24,060
to keep the crab flavor alive in the bread.

1314
01:25:24,190 --> 01:25:27,329
As for the crab pastry on the top,

1315
01:25:27,330 --> 01:25:29,606
we were inspired by the fact that people also eat the shells...

1316
01:25:29,630 --> 01:25:31,500
when they have poo pad pong curry.

1317
01:25:31,830 --> 01:25:33,570
To eat Poo Pad Pong Bread Curry,

1318
01:25:33,770 --> 01:25:36,540
please save the pointy ends...

1319
01:25:36,740 --> 01:25:39,110
for the very last bite.

1320
01:25:39,310 --> 01:25:41,910
That's the best part.

1321
01:25:42,180 --> 01:25:44,640
Thank you. Masters, shall we dig in?

1322
01:25:46,350 --> 01:25:47,780
I feel bad taking this apart.

1323
01:25:48,620 --> 01:25:49,820
It's just too cute.

1324
01:25:50,350 --> 01:25:51,650
I'll put it to the side.

1325
01:25:54,820 --> 01:25:55,890
Gosh.

1326
01:26:22,920 --> 01:26:25,320
I can vouch for this bread.

1327
01:26:25,420 --> 01:26:27,750
It has carbs, protein, and fat. All of it.

1328
01:26:55,210 --> 01:26:58,020
As a restaurant owner,

1329
01:26:58,150 --> 01:27:01,750
and as a person working in...

1330
01:27:02,260 --> 01:27:04,059
the dining and service industry,

1331
01:27:04,060 --> 01:27:07,560
I believe it's very important to bring joy to customers.

1332
01:27:08,660 --> 01:27:11,400
In that regard, this dish...

1333
01:27:14,930 --> 01:27:16,740
just brings a smile to your face.

1334
01:27:20,710 --> 01:27:24,409
I think a dish that can make the customers laugh...

1335
01:27:24,410 --> 01:27:26,350
is very powerful.

1336
01:27:26,750 --> 01:27:29,720
And as you've said, I saved the end for last.

1337
01:27:29,980 --> 01:27:32,290
It was crispy and savory,

1338
01:27:32,590 --> 01:27:36,290
and it went well with the curry, cream, and the fluffy bread.

1339
01:27:36,460 --> 01:27:38,060
I enjoyed it very much.

1340
01:27:38,760 --> 01:27:39,830
- Thank you. - Thank you.

1341
01:27:42,260 --> 01:27:45,500
I personally enjoy poo pad pong curry that much,

1342
01:27:45,800 --> 01:27:48,940
but I really enjoyed your bread.

1343
01:27:49,100 --> 01:27:50,369
And while I was eating,

1344
01:27:50,370 --> 01:27:52,109
I thought I should give...

1345
01:27:52,110 --> 01:27:55,270
poo pad pong curry another try.

1346
01:27:55,480 --> 01:27:56,640
Thank you for your dish.

1347
01:27:57,210 --> 01:27:58,210
Thank you.

1348
01:27:58,580 --> 01:28:00,579
I'm confident in making any type of bread,

1349
01:28:00,580 --> 01:28:02,620
so of course I was confident with breads as a meal.

1350
01:28:03,550 --> 01:28:05,220
Master Narae, what did you think?

1351
01:28:05,550 --> 01:28:07,319
I also like your creativity,

1352
01:28:07,320 --> 01:28:13,059
and I think you did a great job moulding the crab pastry.

1353
01:28:13,060 --> 01:28:16,960
But the problem is that the bread is underbaked.

1354
01:28:21,100 --> 01:28:23,370
It is pretty, but the crab inside is...

1355
01:28:23,800 --> 01:28:24,840
Sorry?

1356
01:28:25,270 --> 01:28:26,510
Why did he bake it like this?

1357
01:28:29,710 --> 01:28:31,480
- It's underbaked. - Yes.

1358
01:28:32,910 --> 01:28:34,080
I was very disappointed.

1359
01:28:37,950 --> 01:28:41,590
I saw that you baked it by layering the dough.

1360
01:28:42,060 --> 01:28:46,129
If you'd used a mold to shape your pastry instead,

1361
01:28:46,130 --> 01:28:48,899
you would've been able to avoid underbaking.

1362
01:28:48,900 --> 01:28:53,170
Because of the underbaked batter and the thick dough beneath,

1363
01:28:53,700 --> 01:28:56,640
the taste of flour was strong.

1364
01:28:58,810 --> 01:29:01,139
I was so shocked to hear...

1365
01:29:01,140 --> 01:29:02,580
that my bread was underbaked.

1366
01:29:02,980 --> 01:29:07,580
I was very disappointed with these technical mistakes.

1367
01:29:17,490 --> 01:29:21,160
It didn't rise as much as you'd practiced, right?

1368
01:29:21,960 --> 01:29:23,100
The crab shell pastry?

1369
01:29:23,730 --> 01:29:25,800
It didn't rise properly,

1370
01:29:26,430 --> 01:29:28,870
and it's one big clump now.

1371
01:29:32,070 --> 01:29:33,310
He must've been in a hurry.

1372
01:29:34,340 --> 01:29:36,040
This was such a rookie mistake.

1373
01:29:36,540 --> 01:29:39,210
I should have been a professional,

1374
01:29:39,450 --> 01:29:41,210
but I messed it up too much.

1375
01:29:42,850 --> 01:29:45,990
I was angry at myself in this mission.

1376
01:29:46,150 --> 01:29:49,190
I want to make this clear. Jin Seo messed up.

1377
01:29:50,760 --> 01:29:54,060
We only have one contender left.

1378
01:29:54,360 --> 01:29:57,360
Fine Dining Baker, Contender Yoon Hwa Young.

1379
01:29:57,930 --> 01:29:59,270
Please come up to the front.

1380
01:30:02,140 --> 01:30:04,769
- In fine dining, he's like the... - The godfather.

1381
01:30:04,770 --> 01:30:05,770
- That's right. - Yes.

1382
01:30:05,771 --> 01:30:09,640
What are we bakers supposed to do when a chef bakes too?

1383
01:30:11,340 --> 01:30:13,780
- I forgot to add salt and sugar. - Let's start from the top.

1384
01:30:18,150 --> 01:30:21,420
- Our team leader was born to lead. - Right.

1385
01:30:27,430 --> 01:30:29,930
Today, I made lobster vol-au-vent...

1386
01:30:30,500 --> 01:30:32,570
using black truffles that are in season.

1387
01:30:34,070 --> 01:30:35,969
I think the most important aspects in a good dish...

1388
01:30:35,970 --> 01:30:38,570
are locality and seasonality.

1389
01:30:38,810 --> 01:30:41,170
Black truffles are in season,

1390
01:30:41,410 --> 01:30:43,640
which is why I wanted to use them in my dish.

1391
01:30:47,150 --> 01:30:48,179
The scent is overpowering.

1392
01:30:48,180 --> 01:30:51,179
And in France, a reveillon is a very important meal...

1393
01:30:51,180 --> 01:30:54,220
held on December 31.

1394
01:30:54,490 --> 01:30:56,919
And vol-au-vent is still being served...

1395
01:30:56,920 --> 01:30:58,960
at important events in the Elysee Palace.

1396
01:30:59,330 --> 01:31:03,230
I wanted to recreate vol-au-vent in my own way,

1397
01:31:03,460 --> 01:31:05,229
which is why I brought in lobsters.

1398
01:31:05,230 --> 01:31:07,329
I made vol-au-vent with truffles and lobster,

1399
01:31:07,330 --> 01:31:09,900
which is as fancy as it gets.

1400
01:31:10,070 --> 01:31:11,170
I hope you enjoy.

1401
01:31:22,550 --> 01:31:24,390
- Look at the sauce oozing out. - The sauce...

1402
01:31:26,890 --> 01:31:28,690
- It's spilling out! - The sauce is really...

1403
01:31:29,890 --> 01:31:30,960
This is amazing.

1404
01:31:41,500 --> 01:31:42,900
The asparagus is good.

1405
01:31:44,940 --> 01:31:45,970
It's tasty.

1406
01:31:48,840 --> 01:31:49,980
The seasoning is perfect.

1407
01:31:50,740 --> 01:31:52,060
It's the perfect temperature too.

1408
01:32:11,800 --> 01:32:13,469
Everyone's eating even though we're all full.

1409
01:32:13,470 --> 01:32:14,630
The plating is amazing.

1410
01:32:15,030 --> 01:32:16,070
It's good.

1411
01:32:17,500 --> 01:32:19,870
- It's fantastic. - Mimi, slow down.

1412
01:32:20,070 --> 01:32:21,110
Thank you.

1413
01:32:21,240 --> 01:32:22,980
- I can't stop eating. - Right?

1414
01:32:28,510 --> 01:32:29,550
Masters,

1415
01:32:29,820 --> 01:32:32,590
it's time to share your thoughts on the bread.

1416
01:32:33,750 --> 01:32:35,050
This is...

1417
01:32:35,590 --> 01:32:38,789
really a classic French dish.

1418
01:32:38,790 --> 01:32:41,790
Having the puff pastry, the lobster, the truffle,

1419
01:32:42,400 --> 01:32:45,360
and the asparagus altogether...

1420
01:32:45,500 --> 01:32:47,870
made me feel like I enjoyed a hearty meal.

1421
01:32:47,970 --> 01:32:49,410
They call you a master for a reason.

1422
01:32:49,500 --> 01:32:52,640
I thought I wouldn't be able to eat because I was so full,

1423
01:32:52,770 --> 01:32:55,310
but I couldn't even put my fork and knife down.

1424
01:32:55,470 --> 01:32:57,310
- I enjoyed it very much. - Thank you.

1425
01:32:59,950 --> 01:33:03,650
Ten years ago, when I was twenty-one,

1426
01:33:04,280 --> 01:33:06,149
I had my very first fine dining meal...

1427
01:33:06,150 --> 01:33:09,020
at Chef Oh Se Deuk's restaurant.

1428
01:33:09,560 --> 01:33:11,860
And just as it was back then, the sauce is amazing.

1429
01:33:12,220 --> 01:33:14,859
I don't think it could get any better than this,

1430
01:33:14,860 --> 01:33:16,229
considering the time limit and the theme.

1431
01:33:16,230 --> 01:33:19,169
So I couldn't help but wonder...

1432
01:33:19,170 --> 01:33:21,399
- how you made this sauce. - Yes.

1433
01:33:21,400 --> 01:33:25,239
As you all must know, French cuisine takes a very long time.

1434
01:33:25,240 --> 01:33:27,609
So we chose to put in...

1435
01:33:27,610 --> 01:33:31,010
as many ingredients as we could to boil down for the sauce.

1436
01:33:31,240 --> 01:33:33,640
That's how we made the sauce rich and thick in a short time.

1437
01:33:33,750 --> 01:33:35,680
And as the chef, I'm so grateful...

1438
01:33:36,050 --> 01:33:37,849
that you enjoyed it so much.

1439
01:33:37,850 --> 01:33:39,450
This is really high praise.

1440
01:33:40,190 --> 01:33:41,889
I enjoyed this bread too.

1441
01:33:41,890 --> 01:33:44,960
But the vol-au-vent is like the Leaning Tower of Pisa right now.

1442
01:33:48,160 --> 01:33:51,129
If you'd taken one layer out of the vol-au-vent,

1443
01:33:51,130 --> 01:33:52,899
or used a deck oven...

1444
01:33:52,900 --> 01:33:55,269
