1445
01:33:55,270 --> 01:33:57,369
it would've been prettier.

1446
01:33:57,370 --> 01:33:58,869
It's a shame it's leaning.

1447
01:33:58,870 --> 01:34:03,179
But the feuilletage was baked perfectly,

1448
01:34:03,180 --> 01:34:06,579
and the lobster flavor in the sauce was very rich.

1449
01:34:06,580 --> 01:34:08,210
I enjoyed it very much.

1450
01:34:08,710 --> 01:34:09,780
Thank you.

1451
01:34:09,920 --> 01:34:13,550
Out of all of the contenders in Bake Your Dream,

1452
01:34:13,850 --> 01:34:16,059
the one who best understands ingredients...

1453
01:34:16,060 --> 01:34:18,489
and knows how to use the right ingredients...

1454
01:34:18,490 --> 01:34:20,590
to create the right flavor...

1455
01:34:20,860 --> 01:34:25,160
is you, Contender Yoon Hwa Young.

1456
01:34:25,700 --> 01:34:26,970
All your dishes were great,

1457
01:34:27,170 --> 01:34:29,039
and this one was amazing as well.

1458
01:34:29,040 --> 01:34:33,270
And if this show was a cooking competition for chefs,

1459
01:34:33,570 --> 01:34:37,910
I would've given you a perfect score.

1460
01:34:38,580 --> 01:34:40,180
But there's just one thing.

1461
01:34:43,520 --> 01:34:46,649
Although it was great, your dish was...

1462
01:34:46,650 --> 01:34:49,190
